## Data structures

Different Types of Data Structures (with examples):

### Structuring with Primitive values

These are the most basic structures of data: Amost no structure, you cannot even have list of things.

### Structuring with Arrays

Is the first read structure we saw, its ideal to store lists of `anything`:

```js
let todos = [];
//add a task
todos.push(value);
//remove a task
todos = task.filter(t => t != value);
```

### Object Literals

Thanks to object literals our tasks can now have status instead of just the task name.
```js
let todos = [];
//add a task
todos.push({
    status: 'pending',
    name: value
});
//remove a task
todos = task.filter(t => t.value != value);
```

